<br>
I don't think people should really worry about the stuff thats going to happen outside of the game, motivated folks will always find a way around the system. Any way you slice this situation its going to cause an initial flood of items and cash to the market.<br>
<br>
There are two primary questions that go with this situation:<br>
<br>
1) Can a player(s) who has saved up enough plat, start up a guild, buy a bunch of primal weapons, some really good armor for 2-3 tanks, and then start skipping content like HoT/NTOV/ST before heading off to fight SoL and PoP encounters?<br>
<br>
2) Since the answer to 1 is yes, would this be a good thing or a bad thing?<br>
<br>
My feeling is it would be good, as it would help eliminate how linear the game has become. <br>
